        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_NoteCreate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to create a note entry in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Common.Note",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table within a SQL Server database. It logs the creation of a note associated with a specific parent entity, identified by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "parentId",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "parentType",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure also logs the operation details into an application log using another stored procedure, "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_AppLogCreate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". It handles exceptions by rolling back transactions and logging error details."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including input validation, transaction management, error handling, and logging. The use of dynamic SQL elements like XML conversion and the integration with another logging procedure adds to its complexity."
        }
      ]
